  "prompt": "Why is bottled water so expensive?",
  "response": "Bottled water is expensive for several reasons:\n\n1. Packaging costs\n- Plastic bottles\n- Labels\n- Packaging materials\n- Manufacturing and transportation of containers\n\n2. Marketing and branding\n- Advertising campaigns\n- Promotional expenses\n- Creating perceived value and premium image\n\n3. Production and distribution\n- Water sourcing and treatment\n- Quality control testing\n- Bottling process\n- Transportation and shipping\n- Retail markup\n\n4. Profit margins\n- Water companies aim to generate significant revenue\n- Relatively low production costs compared to selling price\n- High demand for convenient, portable water\n\n5. Perceived convenience\n- Easy to transport\n- Ready-to-drink\n- Consumers willing to pay for convenience\n\n6. Regulatory compliance\n- Meeting government safety and quality standards\n- Testing and certification expenses\n\n7. Environmental and processing costs\n- Water purification\n- Filtration systems\n- Potential water source management\n\nWhile bottled water is convenient, it's generally much more expensive than tap water, which is typically safe and heavily regulated in",
